            "description": "\"TANDA, a city in the continent of Bengal, and East Indies, in Asia, once the capital of a kingdom. It stands on the E. side of the Ganges, and a little above where that river parts into branches. Here is a considerable trade in cotton and callicoes; the neighbourhood abounds in buffaloes, tigers, and wild game.\" (Seally, 1787, 2nd Vol., s.v. \"Tanda\")",
